## My-i3-bar

a simple bar to show system information

---

look like this:

![demo.png](demo.png)

### Config

You can edit `v2/config.hxx` to enable/disable modules.

all modules use the same struct `g_data_`(in v2/globals.hxx). If you want to add new modules,just take a look at other modules. All modules are very simple.

**Notice**:You should modify `globals.hxx` to specify ` filesystem_monitor` and `PROC_FILE` because every computer have different value.

### Compile

just 

``` bash
g++ v2/main.cxx -o bar
```

No third-part libraries.

### What is `v1`

I don't know i3status's json format so `v1` is just plain text with ANSI escapes,and it displays badly.